[upbeat music fades]

803
00:52:01,321 --> 00:52:02,857
- How's your coffee, Hank?

804
00:52:03,958 --> 00:52:05,125
- Perfect.

805
00:52:05,727 --> 00:52:07,127
Like it is every time.

806
00:52:12,834 --> 00:52:15,770
You ever get scared being
here at night, you know?

807
00:52:15,803 --> 00:52:17,137
All alone.

808
00:52:17,170 --> 00:52:18,472
- Never really think about it.

809
00:52:18,506 --> 00:52:21,676
I just finish my
shift and go home.

810
00:52:23,678 --> 00:52:24,712
Why do you ask?

811
00:52:28,516 --> 00:52:32,587
- This road right here
runs all the way to Austin.

812
00:52:32,620 --> 00:52:36,658
A few towns in between
but not much else.

813
00:52:38,258 --> 00:52:39,927
Started about five years ago,

814
00:52:42,229 --> 00:52:44,431
folks went missing,
bodies showed up.

815
00:52:44,464 --> 00:52:47,835
Travelers, locals, men, women.

816
00:52:49,537 --> 00:52:52,807
[scoffs] No one's
ever been caught.

817
00:52:52,840 --> 00:52:54,207
- Really?

818
00:52:54,241 --> 00:52:56,611
What's got you thinking
about that tonight?

819
00:52:59,212 --> 00:53:00,682
- Just an old man
talking I guess,

820
00:53:00,715 --> 00:53:02,517
making conversation.

821
00:53:07,220 --> 00:53:09,423
- [Levi] Get you
little bunny. [laughs]

822
00:53:11,959 --> 00:53:13,961
Come on now.

823
00:53:13,995 --> 00:53:15,963
Damn, this thing is rigged.

824
00:53:16,864 --> 00:53:18,599
Shh. [scoffs]

825
00:53:22,469 --> 00:53:24,237
Hm. Hm.

826
00:53:25,673 --> 00:53:27,274
Well, well, well.

827
00:53:29,610 --> 00:53:30,945
Evening Hank.

828
00:53:31,579 --> 00:53:32,780
- Levi.

829
00:53:33,881 --> 00:53:36,751
- You are up late tonight.

830
00:53:36,784 --> 00:53:38,953
Busy planning the
town's bright future?

831
00:53:42,422 --> 00:53:43,925
- It's just coffee.

832
00:53:45,258 --> 00:53:46,627
- Mm-hmm.

833
00:53:46,661 --> 00:53:50,297
Tell me, what is it
that you have in mind

834
00:53:50,330 --> 00:53:53,233
for our humble little
slice of heaven pie

835
00:53:53,266 --> 00:53:54,602
we got here?

836
00:53:56,403 --> 00:53:58,906
- Town where folks don't need to

837
00:53:58,940 --> 00:54:00,474
look over their shoulder.

838
00:54:00,508 --> 00:54:04,145
Peaceful, quiet, free
of troublemakers.

839
00:54:04,178 --> 00:54:05,378
- Mm-hmm.

840
00:54:05,412 --> 00:54:07,782
Yeah, yeah, you
know peace and quiet,

841
00:54:07,815 --> 00:54:11,418
that comes in, in all
shapes and sizes.

842
00:54:11,451 --> 00:54:13,955
Same as troublemakers
last I checked.

843
00:54:13,988 --> 00:54:17,191
- Let's just say, I aim to
narrow down the definitions,

844
00:54:17,225 --> 00:54:19,459
make 'em real clear like.

845
00:54:21,028 --> 00:54:22,964
- Huh? Small towns.

846
00:54:23,598 --> 00:54:24,532
Ah.

847
00:54:24,932 --> 00:54:26,634
Oh, yeah.

848
00:54:26,667 --> 00:54:30,071
You know sometimes I,
[sighs]

849
00:54:30,104 --> 00:54:33,241
I sit up at night
thinking about this,

850
00:54:33,273 --> 00:54:34,876
just troubles me deeply.

851
00:54:34,909 --> 00:54:38,679
I mean here you are,
a pillar of the town.

852
00:54:38,713 --> 00:54:40,347
You wanna do good.

853
00:54:40,380 --> 00:54:42,550
Just make everybody happy

854
00:54:42,583 --> 00:54:44,384
and yet you couldn't stop

855
00:54:44,417 --> 00:54:47,155
the one thing that landed
you here in the first place

856
00:54:47,188 --> 00:54:48,388
from happening?

857
00:54:50,457 --> 00:54:52,794
- Didn't know you had
the ability to think.

858
00:54:54,162 --> 00:54:55,997
You looking to stir up trouble,

859
00:54:57,198 --> 00:54:58,833
you're picking the wrong man.

860
00:55:00,101 --> 00:55:03,370
- Lower your quills
now, Hanky boy.

861
00:55:03,403 --> 00:55:05,472
It's just an observation.

862
00:55:07,074 --> 00:55:08,543
- Very perceptive.

863
00:55:09,677 --> 00:55:11,311
- All right gentlemen,
closing time.

864
00:55:11,344 --> 00:55:13,648
I think it's time
we call it a night.

865
00:55:14,782 --> 00:55:15,883
- Hm.

866
00:55:19,921 --> 00:55:21,354
Yeah.

867
00:55:22,156 --> 00:55:23,658
Yeah.

868
00:55:25,026 --> 00:55:26,359
[chair banging]

869
00:55:26,393 --> 00:55:29,429
Your optimism is
truly inspiring.

870
00:55:29,462 --> 00:55:32,200
Tell you what, why don't
you let me cover your tab?

871
00:55:32,233 --> 00:55:33,500
It's the least I could do

872
00:55:33,534 --> 00:55:35,870
for the town's self
appointed tough guy.

873
00:55:36,838 --> 00:55:38,239
- [Hank] Look at you.

874
00:55:38,272 --> 00:55:40,373
I'll cover my own, thank you.

875
00:55:40,407 --> 00:55:41,676
- Eh, suit yourself.

876
00:55:41,709 --> 00:55:45,012
I'm a little short
tonight anyway.

877
00:55:45,046 --> 00:55:46,681
Ha, ha, ha.

878
00:55:46,714 --> 00:55:47,849
Ah.

879
00:55:49,517 --> 00:55:51,052
Y'all have a good night.

880
00:55:51,085 --> 00:55:52,520
Oh, Janet, tell you something,

881
00:55:52,553 --> 00:55:55,323
you are getting
foxier and foxier

882
00:55:55,355 --> 00:55:57,225
every time I see you.

883
00:55:57,258 --> 00:55:59,560
Oh, speaking of foxy,

884
00:55:59,594 --> 00:56:03,631
I ran into an old
friend of ours, Rachel.

885
00:56:03,664 --> 00:56:06,000
Let me tell you,
she is looking fine as

886
00:56:06,033 --> 00:56:07,400
a drawer full of silver.

887
00:56:07,434 --> 00:56:10,304
Mm, mm, mm.

888
00:56:10,338 --> 00:56:12,206
If I, if I bump into her again

889
00:56:12,240 --> 00:56:14,609
I'll tell her you said howdy.

890
00:56:15,343 --> 00:56:18,246
- That's very generous again.

891
00:56:18,279 --> 00:56:22,016
- Good evening,
and uh, careful out there.

892
00:56:22,049 --> 00:56:26,453
There's a lot of shadows
between here and home.

893
00:56:26,821 --> 00:56:28,656
Woo.

894
00:56:34,662 --> 00:56:37,164
[door creaking closed]

895
00:56:37,198 --> 00:56:39,600
- Every time that man leaves

896
00:56:41,135 --> 00:56:42,904
I pray he won't come back.

897
00:56:44,639 --> 00:56:46,841
- Maybe I'll do us all a favor.

898
00:56:48,843 --> 00:56:51,078
[key jingles]

899
00:56:53,381 --> 00:56:57,818
- [Misty] <i>All right, midnight</i>
<i>movers and heart bruisers,</i>

900
00:56:57,852 --> 00:57:01,389
<i>this is your final</i>
<i>lullaby for the night.</i>

901
00:57:01,421 --> 00:57:03,357
<i>If you made it through the night</i>

902
00:57:03,391 --> 00:57:06,527
<i>mm, consider yourself lucky.</i>

903
00:57:06,560 --> 00:57:08,696
<i>Not everybody does.</i>

904
00:57:08,729 --> 00:57:10,698
- [Brian] All right.
Um.

905
00:57:13,968 --> 00:57:14,769
Yeah.

906
00:57:14,802 --> 00:57:16,737
- [April] Wow.
- Check this out.

907
00:57:16,771 --> 00:57:18,471
- Damn. Woo.

908
00:57:18,506 --> 00:57:19,907
Watch out.

909
00:57:19,941 --> 00:57:21,876
That thing's huge.

910
00:57:26,380 --> 00:57:28,716
Something's been killed
with this before.

911
00:57:29,850 --> 00:57:30,918
Great.

912
00:57:31,451 --> 00:57:34,689
[suspenseful music]

913
00:57:36,456 --> 00:57:37,925
God no, please.

914
00:57:38,426 --> 00:57:39,827
I'll do anything.

915
00:57:39,860 --> 00:57:41,162
I'll join you.

916
00:57:41,195 --> 00:57:42,596
Please don't kill me, sir.

917
00:57:42,630 --> 00:57:45,132
- Oh, I've got
other plans though.

918
00:57:47,668 --> 00:57:49,870
- Like what?
- Like this.

919
00:57:58,145 --> 00:57:59,814
Let's get a room, huh?

920
00:58:08,990 --> 00:58:10,358
- Sorry to hear
it didn't work out

921
00:58:10,391 --> 00:58:11,959
between you and Travis.

922
00:58:13,194 --> 00:58:14,295
- Yeah.

923
00:58:14,328 --> 00:58:17,898
Well, we weren't meant to be.

924
00:58:20,534 --> 00:58:22,069
- Heard it was another man.

925
00:58:24,071 --> 00:58:25,072
- Yeah.

926
00:58:27,208 --> 00:58:28,609
You know, rumors...

927
00:58:30,144 --> 00:58:31,679
They love small towns.

928
00:58:34,415 --> 00:58:37,118
No, we just, we didn't work out.

929
00:58:38,119 --> 00:58:39,253
We weren't right.

930
00:58:42,089 --> 00:58:44,725
- Guess some folks don't
have a finish line.

931
00:58:48,162 --> 00:58:49,530
Well,

932
00:58:51,432 --> 00:58:55,870
you uh, be safe
closing up, Janet.

933
00:59:04,045 --> 00:59:06,180
[suspenseful music]

934
00:59:06,213 --> 00:59:07,281
- Night, Hank.

935
00:59:12,586 --> 00:59:14,889
[both giggling]

936
00:59:14,922 --> 00:59:17,625
[door banging]

937
00:59:17,658 --> 00:59:19,827
- Somebody's got bad timing.

938
00:59:19,860 --> 00:59:21,729
- Well, it's
probably just April.

939
00:59:21,762 --> 00:59:24,298
She's probably drunk
and forgot her key.

940
00:59:25,699 --> 00:59:28,969
[suspenseful music]

941
00:59:34,208 --> 00:59:36,777
- All right, you owe
us one now shitheads.

942
00:59:42,551 --> 00:59:45,352
[phone ringing]

943
00:59:51,192 --> 00:59:52,593
How can I help you?

944
00:59:55,429 --> 00:59:56,630
Who?

945
00:59:58,232 --> 00:59:59,633
Oh, I'm sorry,

946
00:59:59,667 --> 01:00:02,571
there's only big bad
psycho killers here.

947
01:00:02,603 --> 01:00:04,338
[phone banging]

948
01:00:12,613 --> 01:00:15,282
[Jess laughing]

949
01:00:15,316 --> 01:00:17,519
- No, no Mr. Monster.

950
01:00:17,552 --> 01:00:19,120
Please don't kill me.

951
01:00:19,153 --> 01:00:22,256
I just wanna go to
the music festival.

952
01:00:22,289 --> 01:00:23,891
Oh, you're a cowboy?

953
01:00:23,924 --> 01:00:26,260
No, I only like big bad cowboys.

954
01:00:26,293 --> 01:00:28,095
This just isn't going to work.

955
01:00:30,664 --> 01:00:33,901
[suspenseful music]
[phone ringing]

956
01:00:40,609 --> 01:00:41,809
Hello?

957
01:00:43,344 --> 01:00:45,679
Yeah, yeah he's right here.

958
01:00:46,780 --> 01:00:47,982
It's your wife.

959
01:00:50,217 --> 01:00:53,254
- So, I'm never coming home...
- No, ever.

960
01:00:55,524 --> 01:00:59,226
[Jess laughing]

961
01:01:06,167 --> 01:01:07,968
[knocking on door]

962
01:01:08,002 --> 01:01:10,738
- [cowboy] You've gotta be...

963
01:01:10,771 --> 01:01:13,508
[banging on door]

964
01:01:13,542 --> 01:01:15,209
[suspenseful music]

965
01:01:15,242 --> 01:01:16,944
- [Jess] Holy shit, Katy.

966
01:01:18,679 --> 01:01:20,047
- [Katy] What are
you guys doing?

967
01:01:20,080 --> 01:01:22,383
- [Jess] Well, take
a fucking wild guess.

968
01:01:24,018 --> 01:01:26,387
Hey, have you seen Chloe?

969
01:01:26,420 --> 01:01:27,955
[door closing]

970
01:01:27,988 --> 01:01:29,558
- [Katy] I haven't seen her.

971
01:01:29,591 --> 01:01:31,492
- [Jess] Where the
hell did she go?

972
01:01:31,526 --> 01:01:34,795
[suspenseful music]

973
01:01:36,096 --> 01:01:38,098
[door squeaking]

974
01:01:56,383 --> 01:01:59,853
[suspenseful music continues]

975
01:02:15,269 --> 01:02:16,270
- Hey.

976
01:02:16,837 --> 01:02:19,306
Hey. [yelling]

977
01:02:19,340 --> 01:02:21,141
Let me out of here.

978
01:02:21,175 --> 01:02:22,409
Son of a bitch.

979
01:02:22,443 --> 01:02:25,412
[panting]

980
01:02:25,446 --> 01:02:27,181
Get me out of here.

981
01:02:27,214 --> 01:02:28,182
Get me out.

982
01:02:30,884 --> 01:02:32,419
- Hey Bubba, how you doing?

983
01:02:32,453 --> 01:02:33,454
Come on in.

984
01:02:38,292 --> 01:02:39,293
What's up?

985
01:02:41,563 --> 01:02:42,763
- Not much.

986
01:02:43,397 --> 01:02:44,865
Just meeting Levi.

987
01:02:52,607 --> 01:02:54,141
There's this girl.

988
01:02:58,613 --> 01:03:00,214
There's something about her.

989
01:03:04,385 --> 01:03:05,986
- Can I tell you a story?

990
01:03:07,589 --> 01:03:09,290
Years ago there was this girl.

991
01:03:10,291 --> 01:03:12,126
She used to come up
here and ride her bike,

992
01:03:12,159 --> 01:03:16,263
her motorcycle and that
girl had so much energy,

993
01:03:16,297 --> 01:03:17,699
so much fire.

994
01:03:17,732 --> 01:03:21,402
I swear that girl
actually told the sun

995
01:03:21,435 --> 01:03:24,071
when to set and when to wake up.

996
01:03:24,104 --> 01:03:26,140
That's what she was like.

997
01:03:26,173 --> 01:03:30,512
It was almost like she
was daring the world

998
01:03:30,545 --> 01:03:33,180
to just disappoint her.

999
01:03:33,914 --> 01:03:36,050
One night we were talking

1000
01:03:36,083 --> 01:03:39,386
and she ended up
saying, you know Red,

1001
01:03:41,322 --> 01:03:44,892
don't let 'em kill ya 'cause
they're gonna kill ya.

1002
01:03:45,859 --> 01:03:49,930
And then she was gone.

1003
01:03:55,869 --> 01:03:57,471
- Think she thinks about you?

1004
01:03:58,506 --> 01:03:59,840
- Gotta hope so.

1005
01:03:59,873 --> 01:04:02,777
[chuckles] That'd be nice but
I mean you know,

1006
01:04:02,811 --> 01:04:04,945
it was such a long time ago.

1007
01:04:05,580 --> 01:04:06,614
- Yeah.

1008
01:04:10,451 --> 01:04:12,052
Hey, did you find the...

1009
01:04:12,086 --> 01:04:13,387
- I took care of that.

1010
01:04:13,420 --> 01:04:14,622
I cleaned it up.

1011
01:04:14,656 --> 01:04:18,992
I'm gonna tell you right now
I'm a little bit hostile at Levi

1012
01:04:19,026 --> 01:04:21,128
because that boy's
getting really sloppy.

1013
01:04:21,161 --> 01:04:22,831
You need to be very careful

1014
01:04:22,863 --> 01:04:24,632
when you go out with that guy.

1015
01:04:26,934 --> 01:04:28,969
You really like this girl?

1016
01:04:33,440 --> 01:04:34,375
Okay.

1017
01:04:34,408 --> 01:04:35,876
Well, go find out.

1018
01:04:39,681 --> 01:04:40,881
- Thanks, Red.

1019
01:04:47,488 --> 01:04:50,290
[door creaks, closes]

1020
01:05:29,096 --> 01:05:32,332
[suspenseful music]

1021
01:05:34,435 --> 01:05:36,403
[April gasps]

1022
01:05:37,639 --> 01:05:38,640
- Hey.

1023
01:05:39,641 --> 01:05:40,675
You dozed off.

1024
01:05:42,911 --> 01:05:44,111
You okay?

1025
01:05:44,546 --> 01:05:45,547
- Yeah.

1026
01:05:48,716 --> 01:05:50,484
- I had a nightmare.

1027
01:05:50,518 --> 01:05:51,820
- A nightmare?

1028
01:05:51,853 --> 01:05:53,120
What happened?

1029
01:05:56,691 --> 01:05:58,827
- Someone killed us.

1030
01:05:58,860 --> 01:06:02,129
- [chuckles] No, I mean I'm,
I'm still here.

1031
01:06:05,567 --> 01:06:06,701
I'm here, okay?

1032
01:06:06,734 --> 01:06:07,936
Nothing's gonna happen.

1033
01:06:07,968 --> 01:06:10,070
Everything's gonna
be all fine and good.

1034
01:06:10,839 --> 01:06:12,039
Trust me.

1035
01:06:13,240 --> 01:06:15,476
- [cowboy] You ever heard
that story about Ricky?

1036
01:06:17,077 --> 01:06:18,278
- Who's Ricky?

1037
01:06:19,346 --> 01:06:23,250
- About 10 years
ago, long time ago,

1038
01:06:24,284 --> 01:06:26,453
there was this guy
named Ricky, all right?

1039
01:06:27,187 --> 01:06:29,022
He used to drive this old van.

1040
01:06:30,758 --> 01:06:32,326
When he was driving it

1041
01:06:32,359 --> 01:06:34,294
these kids started
going missing.

1042
01:06:36,029 --> 01:06:36,698
Guess what they found?

1043
01:06:37,064 --> 01:06:38,398
- [Jess] Hm?

1044
01:06:38,432 --> 01:06:42,336
- [cowboy] Their heads cut off
in the back of his van.

1045
01:06:43,505 --> 01:06:44,873
I'm being serious.

1046
01:06:44,906 --> 01:06:47,074
[Jess mumbles]

1047
01:06:48,375 --> 01:06:52,547
I don't know, but I heard a
rumor that he's back.

1048
01:06:55,015 --> 01:06:57,819
We should probably stay
in and watch out.

1049
01:06:57,852 --> 01:07:01,088
[suspenseful music]

1050
01:07:04,692 --> 01:07:08,295
- You know, I dig you, April.

1051
01:07:20,140 --> 01:07:22,010
Let's get out of here tonight.

1052
01:07:22,042 --> 01:07:24,244
Just us, we can,
we can take my car.

1053
01:07:24,278 --> 01:07:27,147
I've got money saved and
drive straight to Austin.

1054
01:07:30,018 --> 01:07:31,218
I'm serious.

1055
01:07:32,085 --> 01:07:33,186
I think it'd be great.

1056
01:07:33,220 --> 01:07:34,254
We could both
experience the festival

1057
01:07:34,288 --> 01:07:36,056
for the first time together.

1058
01:07:37,424 --> 01:07:39,159
[April chuckles]

1059
01:07:39,627 --> 01:07:40,929
- Let's do it.

1060
01:07:40,962 --> 01:07:42,730
[April screaming]

1061
01:07:43,831 --> 01:07:46,099
- What the hell
are you doing here?

1062
01:07:46,133 --> 01:07:49,136
[door bell jingles]

1063
01:07:57,612 --> 01:07:59,179
- Surprise.

1064
01:08:00,147 --> 01:08:01,883
I got a body in the back.

1065
01:08:01,916 --> 01:08:03,216
Get in.

1066
01:08:05,085 --> 01:08:06,286
[Dallas sighs]

1067
01:08:10,090 --> 01:08:11,526
[van door closes]

1068
01:08:31,946 --> 01:08:34,582
[van engine revving]

1069
01:08:35,049 --> 01:08:37,652
[tense music]

1070
