[knife hits ground]

1330
01:27:33,054 --> 01:27:35,255
- We can be good people.

1331
01:27:35,288 --> 01:27:37,558
If we don't kill anyone anymore.

1332
01:27:39,894 --> 01:27:40,895
- I'll try.

1333
01:27:54,542 --> 01:27:57,512
- [Misty] <i>If you're out there</i>
<i>driving, windows cracked,</i>

1334
01:27:57,545 --> 01:28:00,313
<i>soul just a little bit bruised,</i>

1335
01:28:00,347 --> 01:28:02,517
<i>you're in the right place</i>

1336
01:28:02,550 --> 01:28:04,284
<i>because this is Midnight Misty</i>

1337
01:28:04,317 --> 01:28:07,655
<i>and you're tuned in to</i>
<i>the last safe frequency</i>

1338
01:28:07,688 --> 01:28:09,190
on the dial.

1339
01:28:09,223 --> 01:28:12,425
Tonight feels like
ghosts are hitchhiking

1340
01:28:12,459 --> 01:28:16,631
with old regrets and
outstretched thumbs

1341
01:28:16,664 --> 01:28:19,534
begging for a ride
just a few exits past

1342
01:28:19,567 --> 01:28:21,736
where you were supposed to stop

1343
01:28:22,435 --> 01:28:25,807
but you didn't, did you?

1344
01:28:25,840 --> 01:28:27,875
Nope, none of us do.

1345
01:28:28,810 --> 01:28:30,377
They say the desert
doesn't forget,

1346
01:28:30,410 --> 01:28:32,780
it holds on to heat, secrets and

1347
01:28:32,814 --> 01:28:35,283
<i>sometimes the</i>
<i>shape of the last thing</i>

1348
01:28:35,315 --> 01:28:38,986
<i>that screamed into the silence.</i>

1349
01:28:39,020 --> 01:28:43,291
<i>What have you screamed</i>
<i>into your pillow lately?</i>

1350
01:28:43,323 --> 01:28:46,861
<i>Into your past, into</i>
<i>the ear of someone</i>

1351
01:28:46,894 --> 01:28:50,363
<i>who said they'd never</i>
<i>leave but they did anyways.</i>

1352
01:28:51,165 --> 01:28:54,367
<i>I know baby, I know.</i>

1353
01:28:54,401 --> 01:28:57,738
<i>Some wounds don't</i>
<i>bleed, they just...</i>

1354
01:28:57,772 --> 01:28:59,574
...echo.

1355
01:28:59,607 --> 01:29:02,342
But you're not alone
in that rear view.

1356
01:29:03,010 --> 01:29:04,411
Not tonight.

1357
01:29:04,444 --> 01:29:07,447
We're all chasing
something in the dark.

1358
01:29:08,448 --> 01:29:13,821
Forgiveness, truth, or maybe

1359
01:29:13,855 --> 01:29:16,423
just the right song
to cry into.

1360
01:29:17,390 --> 01:29:19,026
<i>So, keep your eyes on the road</i>

1361
01:29:19,060 --> 01:29:23,363
<i>because not every light</i>
<i>up ahead is a motel.</i>

1362
01:29:23,396 --> 01:29:27,568
<i>Some are just illusions</i>
<i>waiting to burn you</i>

1363
01:29:27,602 --> 01:29:31,371
<i>and some are the</i>
<i>beginning of the end.</i>

1364
01:29:32,807 --> 01:29:36,443
This is your lullaby
for the damned.

1365
01:29:37,444 --> 01:29:40,681
I'm Midnight Misty at 91.7.

1366
01:29:41,315 --> 01:29:44,051
[dramatic upbeat music]

1367
01:30:05,373 --> 01:30:08,408
[sirens blaring]

1368
01:30:11,879 --> 01:30:14,115
- [officer over speaker]
Turn your vehicle off.

1369
01:30:15,283 --> 01:30:17,450
[keys jingle]
[engine stops]

1370
01:30:18,219 --> 01:30:19,419
Yeah, this is Travis Wilkes.

1371
01:30:19,452 --> 01:30:23,190
I got a 1080 on a
black El Camino.

1372
01:30:23,224 --> 01:30:25,326
DL83...

1373
01:30:25,359 --> 01:30:26,627
- Yeah, we'll be
good, we'll be good.

1374
01:30:26,661 --> 01:30:28,495
He's just gonna check my ID.
- Okay, yeah.

1375
01:30:28,529 --> 01:30:29,630
- [Brian] We're on
the way to a festival.

1376
01:30:29,664 --> 01:30:31,032
I'm sure he's pulling
over tons of people.

1377
01:30:31,065 --> 01:30:32,633
- Good, we're almost there.
- [Brian] Yeah, we're almost

1378
01:30:32,667 --> 01:30:34,835
there anyway so he's just
probably gonna give us a pass.

1379
01:30:44,145 --> 01:30:47,214
[suspenseful music]

1380
01:30:48,481 --> 01:30:50,751
[Brian chatting indistinctly]

1381
01:30:50,785 --> 01:30:52,420
- [April] You think?
- I think.

1382
01:30:52,452 --> 01:30:55,723
- [April] Thank you. [laughing]

1383
01:30:55,756 --> 01:30:58,326
- Alright, here we go.
I got my license, everything.

1384
01:30:58,359 --> 01:30:59,894
- [April] Yeah.

1385
01:31:04,432 --> 01:31:06,033
- Where are you two headed?

1386
01:31:22,717 --> 01:31:27,487
- Daddy, I want
you to meet Katy.

1387
01:31:30,324 --> 01:31:35,162
- [Hank] Son, you
guys in a accident?

1388
01:31:35,196 --> 01:31:38,498
- Uh we tried to
kill each other.

1389
01:31:40,034 --> 01:31:42,236
[Hank chuckles]

1390
01:31:42,269 --> 01:31:43,838
- [Hank] Must be true love.

1391
01:31:45,439 --> 01:31:46,974
Good to meet you, Katy.

1392
01:31:49,110 --> 01:31:50,845
Please join us.

1393
01:31:52,213 --> 01:31:53,647
- Nice to meet you.

1394
01:31:58,452 --> 01:32:00,221
[chair rumbles]

1395
01:32:04,291 --> 01:32:05,292
- Where's Travis?

1396
01:32:06,327 --> 01:32:07,661
I want him to meet Katy.

1397
01:32:08,596 --> 01:32:09,997
- [Hank] Uh, he's working.

1398
01:32:12,767 --> 01:32:14,268
Should be home anytime soon.

1399
01:32:20,641 --> 01:32:24,645
Let's bow our head and pray.

1400
01:32:30,519 --> 01:32:33,788
[suspenseful music]
[eerie voices whispering]

1401
01:32:39,060 --> 01:32:41,796
[upbeat music]

1402
01:33:32,179 --> 01:33:35,749
[upbeat music continues]

1403
01:34:23,864 --> 01:34:27,735
[upbeat music continues]